<section class="page-head section section--tight">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow">Research</p>
    <h1>What the research says</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      RCPD is young as a recognized diagnosis, but the evidence base is growing fast. Here are
      key peer-reviewed papers and clinician talks &mdash; useful reading to bring to an appointment.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section__head">
      <p class="eyebrow">Papers</p>
      <h2>Clinical research</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <p class="card__kicker">2019 &middot; Bastian &amp; Smithson</p>
        <h3 class="card__title">Inability to Belch and Associated Symptoms Due to RCPD: Diagnosis and Treatment</h3>
        <p>
          In 51 patients who had long suffered without a clear diagnosis, a targeted botulinum
          toxin injection into the cricopharyngeus both confirmed RCPD and provided dramatic,
          lasting relief &mdash; the paper that put the condition on the map.
        </p>
        <a class="arrow" href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC6572913/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read the paper &rarr;</a>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <p class="card__kicker">2024 &middot; Miller, Lina &amp; Akst</p>
        <h3 class="card__title">Retrograde Cricopharyngeal Dysfunction: A Review</h3>
        <p>
          A clear overview of how the upper esophageal sphincter works, why RCPD is hard to
          diagnose, and current treatments &mdash; plus how patient communities drove awareness.
        </p>
        <a class="arrow" href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC10817096/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read the review &rarr;</a>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <p class="card__kicker">2024 &middot; Malhotra et&nbsp;al.</p>
        <h3 class="card__title">Diagnosis and Management of RCPD: A Systematic Review</h3>
        <p>
          Pooling 17 studies and 637 patients, this review finds botulinum toxin injections
          (often 50&nbsp;units) and, when needed, cricopharyngeal myotomy offer effective relief.
        </p>
        <a class="arrow" href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11474230/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read the review &rarr;</a>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <p class="card__kicker">2021 &middot; Karagama</p>
        <h3 class="card__title">Abelchia: Inability to Belch/Burp &mdash; a New Disorder?</h3>
        <p>
          Examines the diagnostic challenges of R-CPD and shows how targeted botulinum toxin
          injections offer lasting relief and meaningfully improve quality of life.
        </p>
        <a class="arrow" href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8553696/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read the paper &rarr;</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

